=Bio=

Luigino Bruni is Associate Professor of Economics at the University of Milano-Bicocca. His primary fields of interest and publication are the history of thought, ethics, reciprocity and philosophy of economics. He has recently published Civil Happiness (2006) and edited, together with P. Porta, Economics and Happiness (2005).


